	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, the Aladdin was a cool idea.  But it seems kinda dated today, from when ROM strictly meant read-only.  I think a flashcart is a better continuation of what the Aladdin did best, which is lower reproduction costs for future games.  In fact, using Flash lowers that to the cost of perhaps a CD-R at the least.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


